article.headline: Eastern Illinois 57, Morehead State 56
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- George Tandy's rebound putback with 2.6 seconds remaining gave Eastern Illinois a 57-56 win over Morehead State Wednesday night in the Ohio Valley Conference. Trailing 56-55 with less than 30 seconds left, the Panthers (1-7, 1-3 OVC) missed two shots before Tandy hit the put back. Eastern Illinois led 27-17 at the half, but saw the Eagles battle back in the final 20 minutes. Josh Gomes led Eastern Illinois with 17 points Stan Januska hit back-to-back 3-pointers to put Morehead State (1-7, 0-4) ahead 40-37 with 11:09 remaining. The Panthers took a 55-52 lead when Bobby Catchings hit a 3-pointer with 1:14 left. Morehead then went on a 4-0 run on consecutive baskets by Shaun Williams and Cory Burns to go ahead 56-55. Januska and Quentin Pryor each had 11 points for Morehead State.
